stantly by localized cognitive nodes with supervisor exceptions routed to human dashboards.\" }\n132 |         ]\n133 |       },\n134 |       {\n135 |         id: \"process_q3\",\n136 |         text: \"How are process inefficiencies and performance bottlenecks identified?\",\n137 |         options: [\n138 |           { score: 1, label: \"Anecdotal Reporting\", description: \"Addressed only when employees complain or customer dissatisfaction levels spike significantly.\" },\n139 |           { score: 2, label: \"Monthly Retrospectives\", description: \"Middle managers review basic KPIs and timeline bottlenecks on regular corporate calendars.\" },\n140 |           { score: 3, label: \"Live Dashboard\", description: \"Operations track real-time queue lengths and SLA timers via structured visual monitoring platforms.\" },\n141 |           { score: 4, label: \"Multi-Agent Telemetry\", description: \"Active logs trace every cognitive step and latency factor, dynamically pinpointing friction nodes.\" }\n142 |         ]\n143 |       }\n144 |     ]\n145 |   },\n146 |   {\n147 |     id: \"talent\",\n148 |     name: \"Talent & Literacy\",\n149 |     shortName: \"Talent\",\n150 |     color: \"#EC4899\",\n151 |     borderColor: \"border-[#EC4899]/20\",\n152 |     description: \"In-house engineering strength, general AI literacy of employees, and structured transformation management.\",\n153 |     questions: [\n154 |       {\n155 |         id: \"talent_q1\",\n156 |         text: \"What is the level of general AI literacy and operational tool adoption?\",\n157 |         options: [\n158 |           { score: 1, label: \"Low Awareness\", description: \"Employees see AI as experimental or threatening, using it in hidden, unregulated ways.\" },\n159 |           { score: 2, label: \"Basic Copilot Use\", description: \"Broad use of standard commercial chatbots for drafting emails, editing text, or simple web queries.\" },\n160 |           { score: 3, label: \"Internal Portals\", description: \"Teams utilize custom company-approved AI portals built with security guidelines and specific templates.\" },\n161 |           { score: 4, label: \"Coordinated Operators\", description: \"Staff are trained in prompt structures and agent supervision, actively co-working with digital nodes.\" }\n162 |         ]\n163 |       },\n164 |       {\n165 |         id: \"talent_q2\",\n166 |         text: \"Describe your in-house software and artificial intelligence engineering strength:\",\n167 |         options: [\n168 |           { score: 1, label: \"External SIs Only\", description: \"Complete dependence on systems integrators or external consultants for basic software changes.\" },\n169 |           { score: 2, label: \"Generalist IT Teams\", description: \"Competent web and database developers but lacking vector, RAG, or deep model hosting expertise.\" },\n170 |           { score: 3, label: \"Data Science Center\", description: \"Staff data scientists and Python developers building custom models or integrating standard APIs.\" },\n171 |           { score: 4, label: \"Sovereign Engineers\", description: \"Highly specialized engineers managing sandboxes, containerized enclaves, and local runtime models.\" }\n172 |         ]\n173 |       },\n174 |       {\n175 |         id: \"talent_q3\",\n176 |         text: \"How is employee training and organizational friction managed?\",\n177 |         options: [\n178 |           { score: 1, label: \"Friction Ignored\", description: \"Tools are launched without formal enablement, leading to worker confusion and resistance.\" },\n179 |           { score: 2, label: \"Occasional Briefings\", description: \"Broad webinars or introductory slide decks distributed to introduce general AI concepts.\" },\n180 |           { score: 3, label: \"Structured Tracks\", description: \"Tailored educational courses mapping to specific business roles, with sandboxed safe playgrounds.\" },\n181 |           { score: 4, label: \"Adaptive Organization\", de